  description="Agni AI Store is a division of Agni Consulting, a Toronto-based marketing-ops firm. Founded by Aman Gupta. Built for local service businesses across the GTA."
>
  <section class="ai-hero">
    <p class="ai-eyebrow">ABOUT</p>
    <h1>Built in Toronto. By an operator, not an agency.</h1>
  </section>

  <section class="ai-section">
    <div class="ai-wrap ai-narrow">
      <p>
        I'm <strong>Aman Gupta</strong>. I run <a href="https://shopagni.com" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Agni Consulting</a> — a marketing-ops firm that's spent the last decade inside Series-A and Series-B B2B SaaS companies, wiring HubSpot, Marketo, Salesforce, RevOps, demand gen — the unsexy plumbing that decides whether a company hits its number or doesn't.
      </p>
      <p>
        Agni AI Store is the version of that work, built for local service businesses. Vet clinics, chiro and physio practices, HVAC and plumbing operators across the GTA. Same playbook, different vocabulary.
      </p>
      <p>
        I started this division after watching a friend who runs an independent vet clinic in North York lose six figures a year to voicemail and lapsed clients — and realizing the AI + automation stack we deploy at $20M ARR SaaS companies costs basically nothing to run for a 3-DVM clinic. The technology has caught up. Most local-services agencies haven't.
      </p>
      <h2>What I won't pretend to be</h2>
      <p>
        I'm not a vet, a chiropractor, or an HVAC tech. I don't know your medicine, your manual therapy, your refrigerant codes. I won't try.
      </p>
      <p>
        What I do know is the customer lifecycle — the gap between when someone Googles you and when they're sitting in your chair, and every gap between visit 1 and visit 12 where things fall through. I know how to wire that lifecycle so it runs without your front desk having to remember to do anything.
      </p>
      <h2>What you get from me, specifically</h2>
      <ul class="ai-checklist">
        <li>Every implementation in the first 90 days, I lead personally. Not "an account manager."</li>
        <li>The audit is mine. The proposal is mine. The setup is mine.</li>
        <li>After 90 days, an Agni operator runs ongoing ops; I stay on quarterly strategy.</li>
        <li>I'll tell you on the audit call if you should NOT hire us. I send people to direct competitors a few times a quarter.</li>
      </ul>
      <h2>Where to find me</h2>
      <p>
        Email: <a href="mailto:hello@agniai.store">hello@agniai.store</a><br>
        Calendar: <a href="https://calendly.com/aman-shopagni" target="_blank" rel="noopener">calendly.com/aman-shopagni</a><br>
        Parent firm: <a href="https://shopagni.com" target="_blank" rel="noopener">shopagni.com</a>
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>
